                            <comment id="13061213" author="bitstorm" created="Thu, 7 Jul 2011 11:20:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The line of code which throws the exception (AsynchronousDataStore.java:192) is relative to snapshot code o is exactly from RC5.1 version?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I&apos;ve implemented a version AsynchronousDataStore which makes extensive use of java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor class to coordinate saving thread and queue. Using ThreadPoolExecutor you can delegate it synchronization&apos;s issues (it&apos;s a Java 5 class).&lt;br/&gt;
The code is much more simple and I&apos;ve successfully tested id with DiskDataStoreTest. I&apos;ve called it AsyncDataStore in order to easily switch between the current AsynchronousDataStore and my new class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you give my class a chance &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13061266" author="mgrigorov" created="Thu, 7 Jul 2011 12:57:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The code looks OK.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll try it locally and if it is stable then I&apos;ll use it in our performance tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13063843" author="mgrigorov" created="Tue, 12 Jul 2011 12:10:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The previous impl is replaced with Andrea&apos;s impl with r1145561. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
